    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-26T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.515 Gold Bloc/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-26T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 26, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 26—3:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. Am informed that Ryder, American representative on League of Nations
                    Committee on Clearing, had official conversations with Italian Government on
                    tariffs and related questions and stated before leaving Rome he would arrive in
                    London early May to open official negotiations here. I have had very discreet
                    official inquiry here as to his authorizations and should appreciate information
                    to enable me to reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
